The paper deals with probabilistic inference in hybrid networks, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of nonuniform partitioning and the introduction of a new data structure for representing discretization suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The mention of adjusting discretization with evidence and constructing an iterative algorithm suggest a focus on control systems (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT).
